'''Punternet''', also known as '''Punternet.com''', is a [[review site]] that allows customers to rate their experiences with [[call girls]] (customers are referred to as "punters" on the website).<ref name="dailydot.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.dailydot.com/culture/jon-millward-prostitutes-punternet-interview/|title=A British author analyzes what traits men seek in prostitutes|date=26 October 2011|publisher=|accessdate=16 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.economist.com/node/21611074?cid1=d/dsp/Outbrain/dyn/21611074/20150520-00:00am/paid/display-LA/BR-LC/BRPII/none/subs/UK/BR-MIT |title=More bang for your buck |journal=The Economist |date=2014-08-09 |accessdate=2015-09-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/news/latest-news/511425/Punternet-prostitute-reviews-Uk-Arnold-Schwarzenegger-Harriet-Harman-escort-sex-addicts|title=STRIP ADVISOR: Brit sex addicts leaving escort reviews on site even Arnie couldn't kill|date=1 May 2016|publisher=|accessdate=16 February 2017}}</ref>
==Features== The site offers free membership. Free members can submit reviews and access site features and a limited search function.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/society/2014/11/invisible-subjects-men-who-fuel-demand-prostitution|title=Invisible subjects: the men who fuel the demand for prostitution|publisher=|accessdate=16 February 2017}}</ref><ref name="dailydot.com"/>
The site was sold in August 2017 and the new owners dropped the [[discussion boards]] from the site.<ref name="pnet">{{cite web |url= http://www.punternet.com/index.php/ownership |title= Change of Ownership |last= |first= |date= August 2017 |website= Punternet UK |publisher= |access-date= 12 November 2017 |quote= }}</ref> They also changed the site's policy to allow male and transgender service providers to advertise and be reviewed (previously this was limited to female escorts only).<ref name="pnet" />
==Criticism== The site has been met with criticism, most notably in 2009 from [[Harriet Harman]].<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.reuters.com/article/2009/10/01/us-prostitutes-idUSTRE5905CU20091001|title= Schwarzenegger asked to close prostitute Website|publisher= Reuters |date= 2009-10-01|accessdate=2013-11-26 |first=Stefano |last=Ambrogi}}</ref> Harman, who was the [[Minister for Women and Equality]] at the time, asked then California governor [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]] to ban the website, as it was based in California.<ref>{{cite news|author= |url= http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/8282626.stm|title= Terminate degrading site - Harma|publisher= BBC |date= 2009-09-30|accessdate=2013-11-26}}</ref> The web owners thanked Harriet for increasing web traffic to their site.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url= https://www.theregister.co.uk/2009/10/05/punternet_harman/|title= PunterNet thanks Harriet for massive upswing|publisher= Register |date= |accessdate=2013-11-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url= https://www.theregister.co.uk/2010/01/26/punternet_baird/|title= Solicitor General takes fresh pop at PunterNet|publisher= Register |date= |accessdate=2013-11-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/punter-net-prostitutes-thank-harriet-harman-for-publicity-boost-1796759.html|title= Punter Net prostitutes thank Harriet Harman for publicity boost|publisher= Independent |date= 2009-10-02|accessdate=2013-11-26 |location=London |first=Jerome |last=Taylor}}</ref>
In 2018 Trishna Datta, an [[outreach]] worker from [[Ilford]], Essex, launched a petition to have the Punternet website taken down. She said that website lacked adequate safety measures to ensure details which could put sex workers in danger were not revealed. Additionally she expressed concern that some of the sex workers reviewed on the site might be underage or victims of trafficking or sexual assault. Punternet commented that they would report underage prostitutes to the authorities, and that they encourage customers to report underage prostitutes and victims of trafficking to [[Crimestoppers UK]].<ref>{{cite newspaper|newspaper=Metro|title=There’s a vile website that lets people review prostitutes and ‘victims of trafficking’|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/10/04/theres-a-vile-website-that-lets-people-review-prostitutes-and-victims-of-trafficking-8006330/|author=Martine Berg Olsen|date=4 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite newspaper|newspaper=Ilford Recorder|title=‘Prostitute Tripadvisor’: Campaign to close down website in which punters rate and review Ilford, Goodmayes and South Woodford sex workers|url=https://www.ilfordrecorder.co.uk/news/prostitute-tripadvisor-campaign-to-close-down-website-in-which-punters-rate-and-review-ilford-goodmayes-and-south-woodford-sex-workers-1-5721992|author=Ellena Cruse|date=3 October 2018}}</ref>
