{{Infobox recurring event | name = Sarajevo Ramadan Festival | logo = | image = File:Sarajevo.ramadan.festival.jpg | imagesize = | caption = | genre = Religious and cultural festival | date = The month of [[Ramadan]] | frequency = annual | location = Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina | years_active = 2014 - present | founder_name = Sarajevo Navigator Foundation | participants = | attendance = | area = | budget = | patron = | organised = | people = | member = | website = | footnotes = }}
The '''Sarajevo Ramadan Festival''' ({{lang-bs|Sarajevo Ramazan Festival / Сарајево Рамазан Фестивал}}) is an annual religious and cultural [[festival]] held in [[Sarajevo]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] that celebrates the [[Islamic]] holy month of [[Ramadan]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://starigrad.ba/v2/vijest.php?id=4006|title=Na Žutoj tabiji otvoren prvi Sarajevo Ramazan Festival |publisher=starigrad.ba}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=https://akos.ba/otvoren-sarajevo-ramazan-festival-top-sa-zute-tabije-oznacio-pocetak-ramazana/|title=Otvoren Sarajevo Ramazan Festival|publisher=akos.ba}}</ref> The festival was established in 2014 by the Sarajevo Navigator Foundation and the Zone of Improved Business (ZUP) Baščaršija in cooperation with the [[European Union]]'s ''PHOENIX – Culture for the Future'' project. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://sarajevo.travel/en/things-to-do/sarajevo-ramadan-festival/311|title=Sarajevo Ramadan Festival|publisher=Sarajevo Travel}}</ref> It is endorsed by the [[Oriental Institute in Sarajevo]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://sarajevo.travel/en/things-to-do/sarajevo-ramadan-festival/311|title=Sarajevo Ramadan Festival|publisher=Sarajevo Travel}}</ref> The aim of the festival is the creation of inter-religious dialogue and the promotion of peace, reconciliation and solidarity among faith groups through the presentation of Islamic art and culture. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.travnik.ba/fotogalerija-otvoren-sarajevo-ramazan-festival-top-sa-zute-tabije-ozvanicio-pocetak-ramazana/|title=Otvoren Sarajevo Ramazan Festival|publisher=travnik.ba}}</ref>
==Format== The festival lasts for the length of Ramadan and is composed of numerous programmes that are held all over the city. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://darlingitswunderbar.com/2017/06/07/junska-dogadanja-u-sarajevu/|title=Junska događanja u Sarajevu |publisher=darlingitswunderbar.com}}</ref> Open-air [[Iftar]], the evening meal with which Muslims end their daily Ramadan fast at sunset, open to Muslims and non-Muslims alike, is organized every evening in the [[Žuta Tabija]] fortress that overlooks the city. Exhibitions of [[Islamic art]], including [[Islamic calligraphy|calligrophy]], paintings, [[Islamic pottery|pottery]] and [[marquetry]] are held in the [[Gazi Husrev-beg Library]] which also hosts readings of renowned Islamic poetry. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://faktor.ba/vijest/sarajevski-kiseljak-i-sarajevo-ramazan-festival-sire-ljepotu-ramazanskih-obicaja-foto-180881|title=Sarajevo Ramazan Festival širi ljepotu ramazanskih dana|publisher=faktor.ba}}</ref> A trade fair of book publishers on Islamic art is another of the numerous festival programmes. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bhrt.ba/kultura/ispaljivanjem-topa-na-zutoj-tabiji-otvoren-sarajevo-ramazan-festival/|title=Ispaljivanjem topa na Žutoj Tabiji otvoren Sarajevo Ramazan Festival|publisher=bhrt.ba}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.starmo.ba/kultura2/item/54803-ramazanski-sajam-knjige-u-sarajevu.html|title=Sarajevo - Ramazanski festival knjige (RFK) počinje danas u Sarajevu.|publisher=starmo.ba}}</ref> Interactive lectures, pannel discussions and Q&A's on Islamic theology, culture and art are held in the Gazi Husrev-beg Library and the [[Madrasa|Gazi Husrev-beg Madrasa]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mojportal.ba/2014/06/26/sutra-prvi-sarajevo-ramazan-festival/|title=Sutra prvi Sarajevo Ramazan Festivala |publisher=mojportal.ba}}</ref> Lecturers and speakers have included [[Grand mufti]] [[Husein Kavazović]], Islamic art historian [[Sabiha Al Khemir]], German orientalist [[Stefan Weber (Orientalist)|Stefan Weber]] and others. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mojportal.ba/2014/06/26/sutra-prvi-sarajevo-ramazan-festival/|title=Sutra počinje Sarajevo Ramazan Festivala |publisher=mojportal.ba}}</ref> Concerts of different Islamic musical styles such as [[Nasheed]], [[Dhikr]] or traditional Bosnian [[Sevdalinka]] are held in the [[Sarajevo National Theatre]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.klix.ba/magazin/kultura/zatvaranje-sarajevo-ramazan-festivala-uz-burhana-sabana-na-zutoj-tabiji/150716033|title=Zatvaranje Sarajevo Ramazan Festivala uz Burhana Šabana na Žutoj tabiji|publisher=klix.ba}}</ref> The opening and closing ceremonies of the festival are held in the Žuta Tabija fortress. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bhrt.ba/kultura/ispaljivanjem-topa-na-zutoj-tabiji-otvoren-sarajevo-ramazan-festival/|title=Ispaljivanjem topa na Žutoj Tabiji otvoren Sarajevo Ramazan Festival|publisher=bhrt.ba}}</ref>
